						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">(A &amp; (B | C)) | (B &amp; C)</div><br />I am unhappy by the non symmetry of your formula. A, B and C are basically exactly the same thing and should be interchangeable.<br /><br />EDIT: A formula that would seem to work and be symetrical is:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">(A and B and C) xor (A or B or C) xor (A xor B xor C)</div><br /><br />I don't know whether that would be practical.</div>

